Olympus Says Merger Deals ‘Follow Proper Procedures,’ WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-10-17T05:18:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/olympus-says-merger-deals-follow-proper-procedures-wsj-says.html
Olympus Corp. (7733)  said all its merger
deals go through the appropriate channels and follow correct
accounting practices, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing
the maker of cameras and medical equipment.  Michael Woodford said he was fired last week because he
challenged irregularities in a 2008 transaction, while chairman
Tsuyoshi Kikukawa said he was dismissed because he wouldn’t
listen to warnings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  